modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate JSON data, including encoding OCaml values to JSON and decoding JSON strings into OCaml types. Works with OCaml's native data structures such as lists, variants, and records. Used to serialize configuration files and exchange data between OCaml applications and JavaScript environments.

Tracks external dependencies to enable seamless reinstallation and recompilation of packages. Provides an alternative rule for building shared object files from archive files when default behavior fails. Routes predicate flags to the OCaml dependency parser for enhanced build control.

Generates an opam .install file by defining installation rules for libraries, objects, executables, and individual files. It handles paths and sections, allowing precise control over where items are placed, such as bin, lib, or libexec. Use it to map build outputs from an Oasis project to opam's installation structure.
